docs.abstract: Americans are still scarred by the financial crisis, and the fruits of this decade’s record-breaking rally fell mostly to the rich.
docs.snippet: Americans are still scarred by the financial crisis, and the fruits of this decade’s record-breaking rally fell mostly to the rich.
docs.lead_paragraph: The financial system had nearly collapsed. The deepest recession in decades was devouring over 700,000 jobs a month. Roughly $13 trillion in stock market wealth, slowly rebuilt since the dot-com bust, had again been incinerated.

headline.main: The Bull Market Began 10 Years Ago. Why Aren’t More People Celebrating?
headline.print_headline: Little Fanfare as a Bull Turns 10

docs.abstract: February’s meager gain follows other signs of economic sluggishness. But there were encouraging signs in the data as well.
docs.snippet: February’s meager gain follows other signs of economic sluggishness. But there were encouraging signs in the data as well.
docs.lead_paragraph: The economy’s remarkably steady job-creation machine sputtered in February and produced a mere 20,000 jobs. It was the smallest gain in well over a year and came on top of other signs that the economy was off to a sluggish start in 2019.

headline.main: The Jobs Report Was the Weakest in Months. Here’s Why.
headline.print_headline: Weak Job Gains, But Better Signs On Wage Growth

docs.abstract: Regulators are typically hesitant to ground entire fleets of planes. What tips the balance toward doing it?
docs.snippet: Regulators are typically hesitant to ground entire fleets of planes. What tips the balance toward doing it?
docs.lead_paragraph: As the investigation continues into the fatal crash of a 737 Max 8 in Ethiopia on Sunday, regulators in China and Indonesia are grounding the planes, and some airlines in other countries are voluntarily pulling their fleets from service.

headline.main: Some Boeing 737s Are Being Grounded. Here’s What That Means.
headline.print_headline: Some Boeing 737s Are Being Grounded Around the World. Here’s What That Means.

docs.abstract: The Trump administration’s agreement is shaping up to be less ambitious than what the president and his top advisers initially set out to win.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration’s agreement is shaping up to be less ambitious than what the president and his top advisers initially set out to win.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is close to a trade deal with China that would roll back tariffs on both sides of the Pacific but may do little to achieve the substantive changes to China’s economy that the United States initially set out to win, people with knowledge of the talks said.

headline.main: U.S. and China Near a Trade Deal to Drop Tariffs
headline.print_headline: Trade Deal With China May Bring Few Changes

docs.abstract: In a country where wealth usually comes from mining or banking, Scott Farquhar and Mike Cannon-Brookes of Atlassian are a new kind of mogul. And they’re getting into politics.
docs.snippet: In a country where wealth usually comes from mining or banking, Scott Farquhar and Mike Cannon-Brookes of Atlassian are a new kind of mogul. And they’re getting into politics.
docs.lead_paragraph: SYDNEY, Australia — Atlassian is a very boring software company. It develops products for software engineers and project managers, with hits like Jira (for software project management and bug tracking) and Fisheye (a revision-control browser). And who could forget Confluence (an enterprise knowledge management system)?

headline.main: The Strange Experience of Being Australia’s First Tech Billionaires
headline.print_headline: Australia’s First Tech Billionaires See Politics as Up Their Alley

docs.abstract: The former executive, who oversaw compliance with insider trading rules, was accused by the S.E.C. of profiting on nonpublic information.
docs.snippet: The former executive, who oversaw compliance with insider trading rules, was accused by the S.E.C. of profiting on nonpublic information.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — A former senior lawyer at Apple who oversaw the company’s insider trading policies was himself accused of insider trading by federal prosecutors and securities regulators in complaints made public on Wednesday.

headline.main: Former Senior Apple Lawyer Charged With Insider Trading
headline.print_headline: S.E.C. Accuses Senior Lawyer Of Trade Fraud While at Apple
